<SP>
<SPEAKER>Sir <HI>George.</HI></SPEAKER>
<P>That is not enough, Sir&mdash;(<HI>taking Mi&s;s</HI> Dor|rillon <HI>by the hand, and leading her forwar<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"></HI>&mdash;you mu&s;t a&s;k this lady's pardon.</P>
<STAGE>(<HI>Sir</HI> William <HI>&s;tarts, and turns his face away, &s;trongly im|pre&s;&s;ed.</HI>)</STAGE>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Sir <HI>Wm.</HI></SPEAKER>
<P>A&s;k <HI>her</HI> pardon! Though I forgive &s;ome in&s;ults I will not this.&mdash;A&s;k <HI>her</HI> pardon?&mdash;</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Mi&s;s <HI>Dor.</HI></SPEAKER>
<P>Nay, nay, &s;ir George, you have no bu&s;ine&s;s with Mr. Mandred's quarrels and mine&mdash;Re&s;erve your heroic courage for &s;ome nobler purpo&s;e than a poor woman&punc;s reputation.</P>
