<SP>
<SPEAKER>Mi&s;s <HI>Dor.</HI></SPEAKER>
<P>I &s;ee you are both &s;ul<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">en both ob&s;tinate, and I have but one re&s;ource&mdash;Sir George, if you a&s;pire to my hand, dare not to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ift yours again&s;t Mr. Mandred He and I profe&s;s to be enemies; but if may judge of his feelings by my own, we have but pa&s;&s;ing enmities&mdash;bear him no ma<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ice, nor he me, I dare be &s;worn&punc; Therefore Sir, li<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">t but your arm again&s;t him, or in&s;ult him with another word, and our intercour&s;e is for ever at an end&punc;</P>
<STAGE>(<HI>Exit.</HI></STAGE>
</SP>
<STAGE>(<HI>Sir</HI> George <HI>and Sir</HI> William <HI>&s;tand for &s;ome time &s;ilent</HI>)</STAGE>
<SP>
