<STAGE><HI>Enter Lord</HI> Priory&mdash;Bronzely <HI>&s;tarts.</HI></STAGE>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Lord <HI>Priory.</HI></SPEAKER>
<P>I have not kept you waiting, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> hope. My lawyer &s;topt me on bu&s;ine&s;s, or I &s;hould have been here &s;ooner. My dear Mr. Bronzely <HI>(going up to him)</HI> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> thank you a thou|&s;and times for the intere&s;t you take in my concerns; and I come prepared with proper coo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ne&s;s and compo&s;ure to hear the &s;ecret with which you are going to entru&s;t us</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Bronzely&punc;</SPEAKER>
<P>The &s;ecret!&mdash;yes, Sir&mdash;The &s;ecret which I was going to di&s;clo&s;e to my lady Priory&mdash;Ha, ha, ha!&mdash;But, my lord, I am afraid it is of too frivolous a nature for your attention.</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<PB N="37" REF="032304_0037_0FF1BC1FD3F91D08">
<SPEAKER>Lord <HI>Priory.</HI></SPEAKER>
<P>I account nothing frivolous which concerns my wife.</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Bronzely.</SPEAKER>
